The paper discusses the submission and peer-review process used by the First Workshop on Sustainable Software for Science, which is focused on software engineering practices and experiences in the context of scientific research. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the workshop is concerned with sustainability and reproducibility, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Science), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the workshop likely includes discussions of programming languages and tools, which could be relevant to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
